article.headline: Portland State 74, Tennessee State 71
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) --Blake Walker scored 41 points as Portland State held off Tennessee State 74-71 Tuesday night. Walker, a junior forward from San Bernardino, Calif., scored the last four points of the game for Portland State after Tennessee State had pulled to within a point on a pair of free throws by Garrett Richardson with 11 seconds left. Walker came back with a dunk three seconds later, then added two free throws for a five-point lead. Portland State (6-6) took the lead for good in the final 22 seconds of the first half with a 5-0 burst. Bruce Price led Tennessee State (1-10) with 23 points, and Richardson added 19. Jeremy Jackson and Roshaun Bowens each added 10 points. Will Funn was the only other Portland State player in double figures, scoring 10 points. The Vikings have won two straight on the road after dropping 21 straight dating back to the 2001-02 season.
